      "source": "### Network Failure Scenario: Preventing Double Debit\n\n**Problem:** If a withdrawal succeeds (balance deducted) but network fails before confirmation, retrying causes a double debit.\n\n**Real-world Solutions:**\n\n1. **Idempotent Transactions** – Each transaction gets a unique ID. Before processing, check if that ID was already handled.\n2. **Transaction Log** – Store every withdrawal with timestamp + ID. On retry, check the log first.\n3. **Provisional Debit** – Deduct tentatively, confirm only after successful API response, rollback on failure.\n4. **User Confirmation Flow** – Show pending transaction, ask user to confirm receipt of funds before finalizing.\n\n**Example: Idempotent Withdrawal**",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "markdown",
        "id": "b2f261e7-e7d1-4879-aacd-c8b145f8e4c1"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "00695784-cf74-4b5a-aca8-3c4bac2b9921",
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "// Idempotent Withdrawal: Check transaction log before processing\nimport java.util.HashSet;\n\ndouble balance = 1000.00;\ndouble withdrawAmount = 200.00;\nHashSet<String> processedTransactions = new HashSet<>(); // Simulates a database log\nString transactionID = \"TXN-20260221-001\"; // Unique ID from server\n\n// First attempt (normal flow)\nSystem.out.println(\"=== FIRST WITHDRAWAL ATTEMPT ===\");\nif (processedTransactions.contains(transactionID)) {\n    System.out.println(\"Transaction already processed. Duplicate request blocked!\");\n} else {\n    if (withdrawAmount > 0 && withdrawAmount <= balance) {\n        balance -= withdrawAmount;\n        processedTransactions.add(transactionID); // Log the transaction\n        System.out.println(\"Withdrawal successful: -N\" + withdrawAmount);\n        System.out.println(\"New balance: N\" + balance);\n        System.out.println(\"Transaction ID: \" + transactionID);\n    } else {\n        System.out.println(\"Insufficient funds or invalid amount.\");\n    }\n}\n\n// Simulate network failure: User retries with same transaction ID\nSystem.out.println(\"\\n=== RETRY AFTER NETWORK FAILURE (Same Transaction ID) ===\");\nSystem.out.println(\"User retries with same transaction ID: \" + transactionID);\nif (processedTransactions.contains(transactionID)) {\n    System.out.println(\"✓ Transaction already processed. Duplicate request blocked!\");\n    System.out.println(\"Balance remains: N\" + balance); // No second debit!\n} else {\n    if (withdrawAmount > 0 && withdrawAmount <= balance) {\n        balance -= withdrawAmount;\n        processedTransactions.add(transactionID);\n        System.out.println(\"Withdrawal successful: -N\" + withdrawAmount);\n        System.out.println(\"New balance: N\" + balance);\n    }\n}",
      "metadata": {
        "language": "java",
        "executionSummary": {
